Description: The package permits based on a discovery matrix (binary matrix of 
    zeros and ones), to perform an estimation of the number of problems from 
    a Bayesian perspective. In the framework of Value Of Information (VOI), it 
    also allows to assess the economic consequences of undiscovered problems, 
    and to propose an optimal sample size for an additionnal usability test in 
    order to limit the economic consequenes.
